Summary: Networks segment took a $9.1B hit. Global direct-to-conumerous subscribers up 3.6 million
Shares are currently up more than 3%, trading around the $91.80 mark
E-commerce sales surge by 20.2% in July. Net sales for the first 48 weeks of the fiscal year total $229.81 billion
Company plans to use the net proceeds for general corporate expenses.
Bitcoin's market cap was last at $1,081.5659B; Ethereum's was at $2,345.35
Revenue for the quarter came in at $1.90 billion, below analysts' estimates.
E-commerce firm sees Q3 revenue growth in the low-to-mid-twenties percentage range.
Second-quarter dividend unchanged at $0.26 per share. Net asset value as of June 30, 2024 was $11.36 per share
Emil Kakkis is the company's president and CEO.
IPO priced at $4-$5 per share.
